oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Portraits of the 46th Tennessee General Assembly
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: [Giers & Kellein], Photographers
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A compilation of the official portraits of members of Tennessee's legislative body during the years 1886 to 1888. A formal head and shoulders photograph of each member is included. John Price Buchanan of Rutherford County is in the top row, second from right. Buchanan served in the General Assembly from 1887 to 1890 prior to his election as Governor.
